Running the slanConnector_Linux is mandatory to have the AppDemoSim execute correctly, irrespective of whether the user intends to use the packet generator simulation or not.

This utility redirects the simulation ports to the virtual or physical ports. slanConnector is a part of the packet generator simulation tool files.

The SLAN Connector (slanConnector_Linux) must already be running before executing the packet generator Simulator server.

The daemon, slanTunTapLinux together with the daemon slanConnector_Linux help achieve TUN/TAP connections to the ASIC simulator.

pss_unix_utils folder contains all important files to generate slanConnector_Linux.

########################################################################################## Compilation command: gmake all

Product : slanConnector_Linux slanEthPortLinux slanTunTapLinux

Command to run (in background) : ./slanConnector_Linux &

#########################################################################################
